channel.title: aBabe Music Podcast
channel.description:
The aBabe Music Podcast features some of Toronto's fastest rising artists, industry leaders and local happenings, with a touch of nostalgia for where it all began.
Hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman. Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
channel.itunes:author: aBabe Music Babes
channel.itunes:summary:
The aBabe Music Podcast features some of Toronto's fastest rising artists, industry leaders and local happenings, with a touch of nostalgia for where it all began. We are Toronto's collective for musicians and were founded to merge the many pockets of talent that exist all around us.
aBabe Music's podcast is produced by Gord Vickman and hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman.

item.title: aBabe Radio 14
item.description:
The amazing Ashley Cooper joins Lisa, Josh, and Gord in the aBabe Studio to share her incredible story of struggle, success and redemption.  Ashley and her partner Filip launched ABC Charity to inspire children all over the world to create a better future for themselves and their communities.

With Hot Peach, Darcy Windover, The Roncy Boys, and Big Name Actors.

The aBabe Music is made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Hot Peach, Darcy Windover, The Roncy Boys, and Big Name Actors

item.title: aBabe Radio 13
item.description:
Chris Jackson is a promoter, artist manager and a pioneer of Canadian hip hop music.  He joined Lisa and Gord in the aBabe studio to share some amazing and hilarious stories of the earliest days of the scene and why hip hop in Toronto is fun again.

Chris is also the promoter of #BigTicket, The Ultimate Hip Hop Party every month at WrongBar and keeps his "3 P's" poppin' at EasParkPro.

With Dan-e-o (feat. SepTO & Rich Kidd), Maestro (feat. Kardinal Offishall), BMBSHL and Gray.  The aBabe Music Podcast is made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Dan-e-o (feat. SepTO & Rich KIdd), Maestro (feat. Kardinal Offishall), BMBSHL, and Gray

item.title: aBabe Radio 12
item.description: Sarah Burton rolls into the aBabe Studio to play live!  Sarah also talks about things she did not invent and the perils of driving your own car in North Dakota when deers are nears.  Did she hit the animal on purpose?!?  With Alanna Gurr and DCF (aka Prince Caspian).  The aBabe Music Podcast is sponsored by Rad Dude Merch!!  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Sarah Burton, Alanna Gurr and DCF (aka Prince Caspian)

item.title: aBabe Radio 11
item.description:
Marta Pacek joins Lisa, Josh and Gord in the aBabe Studio to tell some stories about her recent Australian tour, why you should never travel with toddlers and the secret of the Bush Bimbos!  

With Marta Pacek playing live!  Also, The Lipstick Junkies and Jennifer LFO (Jennifer Foster). 

Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Marta Pacek, The Lipstick Junkies and Jennifer LFO (Jennifer Foster)

item.title: aBabe Radio 10
item.description:
Zack Leighton is the Executive Director of CIRAA (Canadian Independent Recording Artists' Association).  Their unique programming is sponsored by SiriusXM Canada and is focused on providing opportunity, education and support to Canadian independent recording artists.  Zack shares some insight into how new artists can find established mentors and even earn money for things they're already doing!  

With Maylee Todd, BADBADNOTGOOD, Rich Kidd and Cherry White Music.  

Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Maylee Todd, BADBADNOTGOOD, Rich Kidd and Cherry White Music

item.title: aBabe Radio 9
item.description:
He's a musician, producer, booker and along with his team, the creator of Indie Week Canada and Indie Week Ireland.  Darryl Hurs joins us to share how ten years of work has helped to break independent artists across continents and how it all starts right here at home.  

With Sumo Cyco, Dearly Beloved, Ramin Karimloo, and Scarlett Jane.

The aBabe Music Podcast is hosted by Lisa Humber, Josh Haggarty and Gord Vickman.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Sumo Cyco, Dearly Beloved, Ramin Karimloo and Scarlett Jane

item.title: aBabe Radio 8
item.description:
Nelson Sobral and Jeff Elliott join aBabe Music's Lisa, Josh and Gord to deliver the honest goods on Toronto's music scene.  Invest a few minutes to learn how to keep five hundred billion projects going when most people find it a struggle to maintain just one.  

With Melting Pot, I Hate Todd and Red Falcon/White Lightning.  

aBabe Music's Podcast is hosted by Lisa Humber, Josh Haggarty and Gord Vickman.  Made with love in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Melting Pot, I Hate Todd and Red Falcon/White Lightning

item.title: aBabe Radio 7
item.description: Scott Kenneth Sokoloski from Big Name Actors and Rad Dude Merch has been bringing people together and moving artists forward for almost 20 years.  He has a sit-down and a chin-wag with aBabe Music to share his experience.  Scott knows how to save your money, your sanity and give your career the boost it needs!  With The Histrionics, Bare Claws, Beekeepers Society and Marta Pacek.  Made with love in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With The Histrionics, Bare Claws, Marta Pacek and Beekeepers Society

item.title: aBabe Radio 6
item.description:
Did "we" win a gold medal, or did "they" win a gold medal?  Trouble at the door?  Maybe five bucks is just too expensive!  Finally, one of the aBabe babes gets a Juno nomination!!  

With The Royal Streets, Larra Skye, The Short Films and Alysha Brilla. 

aBabe Music's podcast is hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With The Royal Streets, Larra Skye, The Short Films & Alysha Brilla

item.title: aBabe Radio 5
item.description: What lucrative thing are doctors doing to babies from Sudbury!?  Listen to find out!  With Alysha Brilla in studio, playing live!  Also, Big Name Actors & Kendal Thompson.  aBabe Music's podcast is hosted by Josh, Lisa and Gord.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Alysha Brilla, Big Name Actors and pink champagne!

item.title: aBabe Radio 4
item.description:
Will collaborating with Kendal Thompson mean a one-way ticket to jail??  Have a listen to find out! 

With The DoneFors and Mip and the Mip Power Trio.  aBabe Music's podcast is hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Kendal Thompson, The DoneFors and Mip and the Mip Power Trio.

item.title: aBabe Radio 3
item.description: It's hard to accept, but some animals just don't like you very much.  The boys from Black Rhino Riot join us to explain why.  Also, Shotgun Wedding Band, The Corner and Alysha Brilla.  aBabe Music's podcast is hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Black Rhino Riot, Shotgun Wedding Band and The Corner.

item.title: aBabe Radio 2
item.description: When the apocalypse finally arrives in Toronto, we know the best spot to abandon your Ferrari.  Find out how far five bucks can really take you!  Also, Pastel, The Jing Bang Show and Alysha Brilla.  aBabe Music's podcast is hosted by Josh Haggarty, Lisa Humber and Gord Vickman.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With Pastel, The Jing Bang Show and Alysha Brilla.

item.title: aBabe Radio Pilot
item.description: aBabe Music's inaugural podcast.  Hosted by Josh and Gord on an outdoor patio on a warm summer night.  If local raccoons interrupt the broadcast, should they get a credit?  Have a listen to find out!  Featuring The Love Bombers and Alysha Brilla.  Made in Toronto by Gord Vickman.
item.itunes:subtitle: With The Love Bombers and some nasty urban raccoons.
